+ export function generateSignavioData() {
+   // Simulate October 2025 process mining data
+   const days = 31;
+   const data = [];
+ 
+   for (let day = 1; day &lt;= days; day++) {
+     // Simulate realistic patterns:
+     // - Weekends (days 4-5, 11-12, 18-19, 25-26) have lower activity
+     // - Month-end (days 28-31) has higher processing volume
+     // - Mid-month review (day 15) causes spike in compliance checks
+     
+     const isWeekend = [4, 5, 11, 12, 18, 19, 25, 26].includes(day);
+     const isMonthEnd = day &gt;= 28;
+     const isMidMonthReview = day === 15;
+     const isProcessOptimization = day === 22; // Process optimization initiative day
+ 
+     // Process Efficiency Metrics
+     const baseCycleTime = 4.5; // hours
+     const cycleTimeVariation = (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.8;
+     const avg_cycle_time = isProcessOptimization 
+       ? baseCycleTime - 0.8 // Optimization reduces cycle time
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseCycleTime + 1.2 // Month-end increases cycle time
+         : baseCycleTime + cycleTimeVariation;
+ 
+     const baseThroughput = isWeekend ? 45 : 120;
+     const throughput = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseThroughput * 1.4 + (Math.random() * 20)
+       : baseThroughput + (Math.random() * 30 - 15);
+ 
+     const baseWaitTime = 1.2; // hours
+     const avg_wait_time = isWeekend 
+       ? baseWaitTime * 0.3
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseWaitTime * 1.8
+         : baseWaitTime + (Math.random() * 0.4 - 0.2);
+ 
+     const avg_processing_time = avg_cycle_time - avg_wait_time;
+ 
+     // Process Compliance Metrics
+     const baseConformance = 87;
+     const conformance_rate = isMidMonthReview 
+       ? 92 // Increased compliance during review
+       : isProcessOptimization 
+         ? 94 // Better after optimization
+         : baseConformance + (Math.random() * 6 - 3);
+ 
+     const baseSlaAdherence = 91;
+     const sla_adherence = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseSlaAdherence - 8 // SLA pressure during month-end
+       : isProcessOptimization 
+         ? baseSlaAdherence + 5
+         : baseSlaAdherence + (Math.random() * 6 - 3);
+ 
+     const deviation_rate = 100 - conformance_rate + (Math.random() * 2 - 1);
+ 
+     // Automation &amp; AI Metrics
+     const baseAutomation = 62;
+     const automation_rate = isProcessOptimization 
+       ? baseAutomation + 8 // Optimization increases automation
+       : baseAutomation + (day * 0.15) + (Math.random() * 3 - 1.5); // Gradual improvement
+ 
+     const baseBotExecutions = isWeekend ? 180 : 450;
+     const bot_executions = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseBotExecutions * 1.5
+       : baseBotExecutions + (Math.random() * 80 - 40);
+ 
+     const ai_recommendations = isWeekend 
+       ? 5 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 3)
+       : 15 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 10);
+ 
+     // Process Intelligence Metrics
+     const baseVariants = 24;
+     const process_variants = isMidMonthReview 
+       ? baseVariants - 3 // Cleanup reduces variants
+       : baseVariants + Math.floor(Math.random() * 4 - 2);
+ 
+     const baseExceptionRate = 8;
+     const exception_rate = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseExceptionRate + 4 // More exceptions during month-end
+       : isProcessOptimization 
+         ? baseExceptionRate - 2
+         : baseExceptionRate + (Math.random() * 3 - 1.5);
+ 
+     const baseReworkRate = 5;
+     const rework_rate = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseReworkRate + 3
+       : isProcessOptimization 
+         ? baseReworkRate - 1.5
+         : baseReworkRate + (Math.random() * 2 - 1);
+ 
+     const first_pass_yield = 100 - rework_rate - (Math.random() * 2);
+ 
+     // User Engagement Metrics
+     const baseModelers = isWeekend ? 8 : 32;
+     const active_modelers = isMidMonthReview 
+       ? baseModelers + 12 // More users during review
+       : baseModelers + Math.floor(Math.random() * 8 - 4);
+ 
+     const baseViews = isWeekend ? 120 : 580;
+     const process_views = isMidMonthReview 
+       ? baseViews * 1.6
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseViews * 1.3
+         : baseViews + (Math.random() * 100 - 50);
+ 
+     const baseCollaboration = isWeekend ? 15 : 85;
+     const collaboration_events = isMidMonthReview 
+       ? baseCollaboration * 2
+       : baseCollaboration + (Math.random() * 30 - 15);
+ 
+     data.push({
+       day,
+       // Process Efficiency
+       avg_cycle_time: Math.max(1, avg_cycle_time),
+       throughput: Math.max(10, Math.round(throughput)),
+       avg_wait_time: Math.max(0.1, avg_wait_time),
+       avg_processing_time: Math.max(0.5, avg_processing_time),
+       // Process Compliance
+       conformance_rate: Math.min(100, Math.max(70, conformance_rate)),
+       sla_adherence: Math.min(100, Math.max(70, sla_adherence)),
+       deviation_rate: Math.min(30, Math.max(0, deviation_rate)),
+       // Automation &amp; AI
+       automation_rate: Math.min(100, Math.max(40, automation_rate)),
+       bot_executions: Math.max(50, Math.round(bot_executions)),
+       ai_recommendations: Math.max(0, Math.round(ai_recommendations)),
+       // Process Intelligence
+       process_variants: Math.max(15, Math.round(process_variants)),
+       exception_rate: Math.min(20, Math.max(2, exception_rate)),
+       rework_rate: Math.min(15, Math.max(1, rework_rate)),
+       first_pass_yield: Math.min(100, Math.max(80, first_pass_yield)),
+       // User Engagement
+       active_modelers: Math.max(5, Math.round(active_modelers)),
+       process_views: Math.max(50, Math.round(process_views)),
+       collaboration_events: Math.max(5, Math.round(collaboration_events))
+     });
+   }
+ 
+   return data;
+ }
+

+ import {
+   Chart as ChartJS,
+   CategoryScale,
+   LinearScale,
+   LineElement,
+   PointElement,
+   Title,
+   Tooltip,
+   Legend,
+ } from &#39;chart.js&#39;;
+ import { Line } from &#39;react-chartjs-2&#39;;
+ import { signavioMetrics } from &#39;../../data/signavioMetricsData&#39;;
+ import styles from &#39;../../styles/pages/Signavio.module.css&#39;;
+ 
+ ChartJS.register(
+   CategoryScale,
+   LinearScale,
+   LineElement,
+   PointElement,
+   Title,
+   Tooltip,
+   Legend
+ );
+ 
+ function SignavioChart({ data, visibleMetrics, yAxisDomain }) {
+   const chartData = {
+     labels: data.map(d =&gt; d.day),
+     datasets: signavioMetrics
+       .filter(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key])
+       .map(metric =&gt; ({
+         label: metric.name,
+         data: data.map(d =&gt; d[metric.key]),
+         borderColor: metric.color,
+         backgroundColor: metric.color,
+         borderWidth: metric.strokeWidth,
+         borderDash: metric.strokeDasharray || [],
+         pointRadius: metric.key === &#39;conformance_rate&#39; ? 4 : 0,
+         pointHoverRadius: 6,
+         tension: 0.3,
+         fill: false
+       }))
+   };
+ 
+   const options = {
+     responsive: true,
+     maintainAspectRatio: false,
+     interaction: {
+       mode: &#39;index&#39;,
+       intersect: false,
+     },
+     plugins: {
+       legend: {
+         display: true,
+         position: &#39;bottom&#39;,
+         labels: {
+           usePointStyle: true,
+           boxWidth: 10
+         }
+       },
+       tooltip: {
+         backgroundColor: &#39;rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)&#39;,
+         titleColor: &#39;#2c3e50&#39;,
+         bodyColor: &#39;#2c3e50&#39;,
+         borderColor: &#39;#ddd&#39;,
+         borderWidth: 1,
+         padding: 12,
+         callbacks: {
+           title: (context) =&gt; &#96;Day ${context[0].label}&#96;,
+           label: (context) =&gt; {
+             const metric = signavioMetrics.find(m =&gt; m.name === context.dataset.label);
+             const value = typeof context.raw === &#39;number&#39; ? context.raw.toFixed(2) : context.raw;
+             return &#96;${context.dataset.label}: ${value} ${metric ? metric.unit : &#39;&#39;}&#96;;
+           }
+         }
+       }
+     },
+     scales: {
+       x: {
+         title: {
+           display: true,
+           text: &#39;Day of October 2025&#39;
+         },
+         grid: {
+           color: &#39;#ecf0f1&#39;
+         }
+       },
+       y: {
+         title: {
+           display: true,
+           text: &#39;Value (%, hours, counts)&#39;
+         },
+         grid: {
+           color: &#39;#ecf0f1&#39;
+         },
+         beginAtZero: true,
+         min: yAxisDomain[0] === &#39;auto&#39; ? undefined : yAxisDomain[0],
+         max: yAxisDomain[1] === &#39;auto&#39; ? undefined : yAxisDomain[1]
+       }
+     }
+   };
+ 
+   return (
+     &lt;div className={styles.signavioChartContainer}&gt;
+       &lt;Line data={chartData} options={options} /&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;
+   );
+ }
+ 
+ export default SignavioChart;
+

+ import { useState, useMemo } from &#39;react&#39;;
+ import { generateSignavioData } from &#39;../../data/signavioDataGenerator&#39;;
+ import { signavioMetrics } from &#39;../../data/signavioMetricsData&#39;;
+ 
+ export function useSignavioChart() {
+   const [data] = useState(() =&gt; generateSignavioData());
+   const [visibleMetrics, setVisibleMetrics] = useState(() =&gt;
+     signavioMetrics.reduce((acc, m) =&gt; ({ ...acc, [m.key]: true }), {})
+   );
+   const [scale, setScale] = useState(&#39;auto&#39;);
+ 
+   const yAxisDomain = useMemo(() =&gt; {
+     if (scale === &#39;auto&#39;) return [&#39;auto&#39;, &#39;auto&#39;];
+     
+     const visibleData = data.flatMap(d =&gt; 
+       signavioMetrics
+         .filter(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key])
+         .map(m =&gt; d[m.key])
+         .filter(v =&gt; typeof v === &#39;number&#39;)
+     );
+     
+     if (visibleData.length === 0) return [0, 100];
+     
+     const min = Math.min(...visibleData);
+     const max = Math.max(...visibleData);
+     const padding = (max - min) * 0.1;
+     
+     return [Math.max(0, min - padding), max + padding];
+   }, [data, visibleMetrics, scale]);
+ 
+   const toggleMetric = (key) =&gt; {
+     setVisibleMetrics(prev =&gt; ({ ...prev, [key]: !prev[key] }));
+   };
+ 
+   const toggleCategory = (category) =&gt; {
+     const categoryMetrics = signavioMetrics.filter(m =&gt; m.category === category);
+     const allVisible = categoryMetrics.every(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key]);
+     
+     setVisibleMetrics(prev =&gt; {
+       const updated = { ...prev };
+       categoryMetrics.forEach(m =&gt; {
+         updated[m.key] = !allVisible;
+       });
+       return updated;
+     });
+   };
+ 
+   return {
+     data,
+     visibleMetrics,
+     scale,
+     setScale,
+     yAxisDomain,
+     toggleMetric,
+     toggleCategory
+   };
+ }
+ 
```

</details>

+ # SaaS Subscription Page Pattern
+ 
+ This document describes the reusable pattern for creating SaaS subscription product pages (like PaPM, Signavio, SAC, etc.) in the Cloud FinOps application.
+ 
+ ## Architecture Overview
+ 
+ Each SaaS product page follows a consistent structure with these components:
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ src/pages/{ProductName}/
+ ├── index.jsx                 # Main page component (composition)
+ ├── {ProductName}Header.jsx   # Page header with title and context
+ ├── {ProductName}Sidebar.jsx  # Metric controls with accordion groups
+ ├── {ProductName}Chart.jsx    # Time-series chart visualization
+ ├── {ProductName}Insights.jsx # Key observations with period selector
+ ├── {ProductName}Formula.jsx  # Product-specific technical details (optional)
+ └── use{ProductName}Chart.js  # Custom hook for chart state management
+ 
+ src/data/
+ ├── {productName}MetricsData.js   # Metric definitions
+ ├── {productName}DataGenerator.js # Time-series data generation
+ └── {productName}InsightsData.js  # Period-based insights
+ 
+ src/styles/pages/
+ └── {ProductName}.module.css      # Page-specific styles
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Step-by-Step Implementation Guide
+ 
+ ### Step 1: Define Metrics (&#96;src/data/{productName}MetricsData.js&#96;)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;javascript
+ export const {productName}Metrics = [
+   {
+     key: &#39;metric_key&#39;,           // Unique identifier
+     name: &#39;Display Name&#39;,        // Human-readable name
+     color: &#39;#hexcolor&#39;,          // Chart line color
+     category: &#39;Category Name&#39;,   // Accordion group
+     unit: &#39;unit&#39;,                // Display unit (GB, %, hours, etc.)
+     strokeWidth: 2,              // Line thickness (1-3)
+     strokeDasharray: [5, 5]      // Optional: dashed line pattern
+   },
+   // ... more metrics
+ ];
+ 
+ export const {productName}Categories = [
+   &#39;Category 1&#39;,
+   &#39;Category 2&#39;,
+   // ... category names in display order
+ ];
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Step 2: Create Data Generator (&#96;src/data/{productName}DataGenerator.js&#96;)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;javascript
+ export function generate{ProductName}Data() {
+   const days = 31; // October 2025
+   const data = [];
+ 
+   for (let day = 1; day &lt;= days; day++) {
+     // Generate realistic patterns based on:
+     // - Weekends (lower activity)
+     // - Month-end (higher volume)
+     // - Special events (spikes/dips)
+     
+     data.push({
+       day,
+       metric_key: calculatedValue,
+       // ... all metrics
+     });
+   }
+ 
+   return data;
+ }
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Step 3: Create Insights (&#96;src/data/{productName}InsightsData.js&#96;)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;javascript
+ export const {productName}Insights = {
+   &#39;last-month&#39;: [
+     {
+       title: &#39;Insight Title&#39;,
+       text: &#39;Detailed observation text...&#39;,
+       color: &#39;#hexcolor&#39;,      // Border color
+       bg: &#39;#bgColor&#39;,          // Background color
+       textColor: &#39;#textColor&#39;  // Text color
+     },
+     // ... more insights
+   ],
+   &#39;last-3-months&#39;: [...],
+   &#39;last-6-months&#39;: [...],
+   &#39;last-year&#39;: [...]
+ };
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Step 4: Create Components
+ 
+ #### Header Component
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;jsx
+ import Icon from &#39;../../components/ui/Icon&#39;;
+ import styles from &#39;../../styles/pages/{ProductName}.module.css&#39;;
+ 
+ function {ProductName}Header() {
+   return (
+     &lt;div className={styles.{productName}Header}&gt;
+       &lt;h1&gt;&lt;Icon name=&quot;icon-name&quot; size=&quot;large&quot; /&gt; Product Full Name&lt;/h1&gt;
+       &lt;p&gt;Month Year - Description of what the dashboard shows&lt;/p&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;
+   );
+ }
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ #### Sidebar Component
+ Copy from &#96;SignavioSidebar.jsx&#96; or &#96;PaPMSidebar.jsx&#96; and update imports.
+ 
+ #### Chart Component
+ Copy from &#96;SignavioChart.jsx&#96; and update imports/metrics reference.
+ 
+ #### Insights Component
+ Copy from &#96;SignavioInsights.jsx&#96; and update imports.
+ 
+ #### Domain-Specific Component (Optional)
+ Create a unique component that explains product-specific concepts:
+ - PaPM: &#96;PaPMFormula.jsx&#96; - Memory calculation formulas
+ - Signavio: &#96;SignavioProcessFlow.jsx&#96; - Process flow visualization
+ 
+ ### Step 5: Create Custom Hook (&#96;use{ProductName}Chart.js&#96;)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;javascript
+ import { useState, useMemo } from &#39;react&#39;;
+ import { generate{ProductName}Data } from &#39;../../data/{productName}DataGenerator&#39;;
+ import { {productName}Metrics } from &#39;../../data/{productName}MetricsData&#39;;
+ 
+ export function use{ProductName}Chart() {
+   const [data] = useState(() =&gt; generate{ProductName}Data());
+   const [visibleMetrics, setVisibleMetrics] = useState(() =&gt;
+     {productName}Metrics.reduce((acc, m) =&gt; ({ ...acc, [m.key]: true }), {})
+   );
+   const [scale, setScale] = useState(&#39;auto&#39;);
+ 
+   // ... yAxisDomain calculation, toggleMetric, toggleCategory
+ 
+   return { data, visibleMetrics, scale, setScale, yAxisDomain, toggleMetric, toggleCategory };
+ }
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ### Step 6: Create Styles
+ 
+ Copy &#96;Signavio.module.css&#96; and rename all class prefixes from &#96;signavio&#96; to &#96;{productName}&#96;.
+ 
+ ### Step 7: Compose Main Page (&#96;index.jsx&#96;)
+ 
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;jsx
+ import {ProductName}Header from &#39;./{ProductName}Header&#39;;
+ import {ProductName}Sidebar from &#39;./{ProductName}Sidebar&#39;;
+ import {ProductName}Chart from &#39;./{ProductName}Chart&#39;;
+ import {ProductName}Insights from &#39;./{ProductName}Insights&#39;;
+ import {ProductName}SpecialSection from &#39;./{ProductName}SpecialSection&#39;;
+ import { use{ProductName}Chart } from &#39;./use{ProductName}Chart&#39;;
+ import styles from &#39;../../styles/pages/{ProductName}.module.css&#39;;
+ 
+ function {ProductName}() {
+   const { data, visibleMetrics, scale, setScale, yAxisDomain, toggleMetric, toggleCategory } = use{ProductName}Chart();
+ 
+   return (
+     &lt;div className={styles.{productName}Container}&gt;
+       &lt;{ProductName}Header /&gt;
+       &lt;div className={styles.{productName}DashboardLayout}&gt;
+         &lt;{ProductName}Sidebar
+           visibleMetrics={visibleMetrics}
+           scale={scale}
+           onScaleChange={setScale}
+           onToggleMetric={toggleMetric}
+           onToggleCategory={toggleCategory}
+         /&gt;
+         &lt;div className={styles.{productName}MainContent}&gt;
+           &lt;{ProductName}Chart data={data} visibleMetrics={visibleMetrics} yAxisDomain={yAxisDomain} /&gt;
+           &lt;{ProductName}Insights /&gt;
+           &lt;{ProductName}SpecialSection /&gt;
+         &lt;/div&gt;
+       &lt;/div&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;
+   );
+ }
+ 
+ export default {ProductName};
+ &#96;&#96;&#96;
+ 
+ ## Existing Implementations
+ 
+ | Product | Folder | Unique Feature |
+ |---------|--------|----------------|
+ | PaPM | &#96;src/pages/PaPM/&#96; | Formula section with SQL queries |
+ | Signavio | &#96;src/pages/Signavio/&#96; | Process flow visualization |
+ 
+ ## Metrics Design Guidelines
+ 
+ ### Color Palette
+ Use distinct colors per category. Suggested base colors:
+ - Red family: &#96;#e74c3c&#96;, &#96;#c0392b&#96;
+ - Blue family: &#96;#3498db&#96;, &#96;#2980b9&#96;
+ - Green family: &#96;#27ae60&#96;, &#96;#16a085&#96;
+ - Orange family: &#96;#f39c12&#96;, &#96;#e67e22&#96;, &#96;#d35400&#96;
+ - Purple family: &#96;#9b59b6&#96;, &#96;#8e44ad&#96;
+ - Gray family: &#96;#34495e&#96;, &#96;#7f8c8d&#96;, &#96;#2c3e50&#96;
+ 
+ ### Line Styles
+ - **Solid lines**: Primary metrics
+ - **Dashed [5,5]**: Secondary/derived metrics
+ - **Dashed [8,4]**: External system metrics
+ - **Dashed [3,3]**: Calculated/intelligence metrics
+ - **Dashed [10,2]**: User engagement metrics
+ 
+ ### Units
+ Common units: &#96;GB&#96;, &#96;%&#96;, &#96;hours&#96;, &#96;count&#96;, &#96;processes/day&#96;, &#96;runs/day&#96;, &#96;users&#96;, &#96;views/day&#96;
+ 
+ ## Navigation Integration
+ 
+ Routes and navigation are already configured. New pages appear automatically in the SaaS Subscriptions dropdown. See:
+ - &#96;src/constants/views.js&#96; - View ID constants
+ - &#96;src/config/navigation.config.js&#96; - Navigation structure
+ - &#96;src/config/routes.config.js&#96; - Route definitions
+

+ export function generateSACData() {
+   // Simulate October 2025 SAP Analytics Cloud usage data
+   const days = 31;
+   const data = [];
+ 
+   for (let day = 1; day &lt;= days; day++) {
+     // Simulate realistic patterns:
+     // - Weekends (days 4-5, 11-12, 18-19, 25-26) have lower activity
+     // - Month-end (days 28-31) has higher planning activity
+     // - Mid-month (day 15) has reporting surge
+     // - Monday spikes (days 6, 13, 20, 27) for weekly reviews
+     
+     const isWeekend = [4, 5, 11, 12, 18, 19, 25, 26].includes(day);
+     const isMonthEnd = day &gt;= 28;
+     const isMidMonth = day === 15;
+     const isMonday = [6, 13, 20, 27].includes(day);
+     const isQuarterlyReview = day === 10; // Quarterly business review
+ 
+     // Content Consumption Metrics
+     const baseStoryViews = isWeekend ? 120 : 850;
+     const story_views = isMonday 
+       ? baseStoryViews * 1.4 + (Math.random() * 100)
+       : isQuarterlyReview
+         ? baseStoryViews * 1.8
+         : baseStoryViews + (Math.random() * 150 - 75);
+ 
+     const baseDashboardAccess = isWeekend ? 80 : 420;
+     const dashboard_access = isMidMonth 
+       ? baseDashboardAccess * 1.5
+       : baseDashboardAccess + (Math.random() * 80 - 40);
+ 
+     const baseReportExports = isWeekend ? 15 : 95;
+     const report_exports = isMidMonth 
+       ? baseReportExports * 2.2 // Monthly reporting
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseReportExports * 1.6
+         : baseReportExports + (Math.random() * 30 - 15);
+ 
+     const baseScheduledPubs = 45;
+     const scheduled_publications = isMidMonth 
+       ? baseScheduledPubs * 1.8
+       : baseScheduledPubs + (Math.random() * 15 - 7);
+ 
+     // User Activity Metrics
+     const baseActiveUsers = isWeekend ? 35 : 145;
+     const active_users = isQuarterlyReview 
+       ? baseActiveUsers + 45 // More users for quarterly review
+       : isMonday 
+         ? baseActiveUsers + 20
+         : baseActiveUsers + Math.floor(Math.random() * 25 - 12);
+ 
+     const baseSessionDuration = 18; // minutes
+     const avg_session_duration = isQuarterlyReview 
+       ? baseSessionDuration + 12
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseSessionDuration + 8
+         : baseSessionDuration + (Math.random() * 6 - 3);
+ 
+     const baseBIUsers = isWeekend ? 28 : 98;
+     const bi_users = isMonday 
+       ? baseBIUsers + 15
+       : baseBIUsers + Math.floor(Math.random() * 20 - 10);
+ 
+     const basePlanningUsers = isWeekend ? 8 : 47;
+     const planning_users = isMonthEnd 
+       ? basePlanningUsers + 25 // Planning surge at month-end
+       : basePlanningUsers + Math.floor(Math.random() * 12 - 6);
+ 
+     // Data &amp; Performance Metrics
+     const baseQueryTime = 2.4; // seconds
+     const avg_query_time = isQuarterlyReview 
+       ? baseQueryTime + 1.5 // Heavy load
+       : isMonthEnd 
+         ? baseQueryTime + 0.8
+         : baseQueryTime + (Math.random() * 0.8 - 0.4);
+ 
+     const baseDataRefresh = isWeekend ? 25 : 85;
+     const data_refresh_count = isMidMonth 
+       ? baseDataRefresh * 1.6
+       : baseDataRefresh + (Math.random() * 20 - 10);
+ 
+     const baseModelLoad = 3.2; // seconds
+     const model_load_time = isQuarterlyReview 
+       ? baseModelLoad + 1.8
+       : baseModelLoad + (Math.random() * 1.2 - 0.6);
+ 
+     const baseCacheHit = 78; // %
+     const cache_hit_rate = isMonday 
+       ? baseCacheHit - 8 // Cache cold after weekend
+       : baseCacheHit + (Math.random() * 10 - 5);
+ 
+     // Planning Operations Metrics
+     const basePlanningSessions = isWeekend ? 12 : 65;
+     const planning_sessions = isMonthEnd 
+       ? basePlanningSessions * 2.2 // Month-end planning surge
+       : basePlanningSessions + (Math.random() * 20 - 10);
+ 
+     const baseInputCompletion = 72; // %
+     const input_task_completion = isMonthEnd 
+       ? Math.min(98, baseInputCompletion + 20) // Rush to complete
+       : baseInputCompletion + (Math.random() * 15 - 7);
+ 
+     const baseVersionComparisons = isWeekend ? 5 : 28;
+     const version_comparisons = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseVersionComparisons * 2.5
+       : baseVersionComparisons + (Math.random() * 10 - 5);
+ 
+     const baseWorkflowTasks = isWeekend ? 8 : 42;
+     const workflow_tasks = isMonthEnd 
+       ? baseWorkflowTasks * 1.8
+       : baseWorkflowTasks + (Math.random() * 15 - 7);
+ 
+     // System Utilization Metrics
+     const baseStorage = 245 + (day * 0.8); // Gradual growth
+     const storage_used = baseStorage + (Math.random() * 5 - 2.5);
+ 
+     const baseAPICalls = isWeekend ? 1200 : 5800;
+     const api_calls = isQuarterlyReview 
+       ? baseAPICalls * 1.6
+       : baseAPICalls + (Math.random() * 800 - 400);
+ 
+     const baseEmbeddedViews = isWeekend ? 45 : 320;
+     const embedded_views = isMonday 
+       ? baseEmbeddedViews * 1.3
+       : baseEmbeddedViews + (Math.random() * 60 - 30);
+ 
+     data.push({
+       day,
+       // Content Consumption
+       story_views: Math.max(50, Math.round(story_views)),
+       dashboard_access: Math.max(30, Math.round(dashboard_access)),
+       report_exports: Math.max(5, Math.round(report_exports)),
+       scheduled_publications: Math.max(20, Math.round(scheduled_publications)),
+       // User Activity
+       active_users: Math.max(20, Math.round(active_users)),
+       avg_session_duration: Math.max(5, parseFloat(avg_session_duration.toFixed(1))),
+       bi_users: Math.max(15, Math.round(bi_users)),
+       planning_users: Math.max(5, Math.round(planning_users)),
+       // Data &amp; Performance
+       avg_query_time: Math.max(0.5, parseFloat(avg_query_time.toFixed(2))),
+       data_refresh_count: Math.max(10, Math.round(data_refresh_count)),
+       model_load_time: Math.max(1, parseFloat(model_load_time.toFixed(2))),
+       cache_hit_rate: Math.min(95, Math.max(60, parseFloat(cache_hit_rate.toFixed(1)))),
+       // Planning Operations
+       planning_sessions: Math.max(5, Math.round(planning_sessions)),
+       input_task_completion: Math.min(100, Math.max(50, parseFloat(input_task_completion.toFixed(1)))),
+       version_comparisons: Math.max(2, Math.round(version_comparisons)),
+       workflow_tasks: Math.max(3, Math.round(workflow_tasks)),
+       // System Utilization
+       storage_used: parseFloat(storage_used.toFixed(1)),
+       api_calls: Math.max(500, Math.round(api_calls)),
+       embedded_views: Math.max(20, Math.round(embedded_views))
+     });
+   }
+ 
+   return data;
+ }
+

+ 
+ function SACSidebar({ visibleMetrics, scale, onScaleChange, onToggleMetric, onToggleCategory }) {
+   const [expandedCategories, setExpandedCategories] = useState(
+     sacCategories.reduce((acc, cat) =&gt; ({ ...acc, [cat]: true }), {})
+   );
+ 
+   const toggleExpand = (cat) =&gt; {
+     setExpandedCategories(prev =&gt; ({ ...prev, [cat]: !prev[cat] }));
+   };
+ 
+   return (
+     &lt;div className={styles.sacSidebar}&gt;
+       &lt;div className={styles.sacControls}&gt;
+         &lt;div className={styles.controlsHeader}&gt;
+           &lt;h3&gt;Analytics Metrics&lt;/h3&gt;
+           &lt;div className={styles.scaleControl}&gt;
+             &lt;label&gt;Y-Axis Scale:&lt;/label&gt;
+             &lt;select value={scale} onChange={(e) =&gt; onScaleChange(e.target.value)}&gt;
+               &lt;option value=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Auto Scale&lt;/option&gt;
+               &lt;option value=&quot;fit&quot;&gt;Fit to Visible&lt;/option&gt;
+             &lt;/select&gt;
+           &lt;/div&gt;
+         &lt;/div&gt;
+ 
+         &lt;div className={styles.accordionContainer}&gt;
+           {sacCategories.map(cat =&gt; {
+             const catMetrics = sacMetrics.filter(m =&gt; m.category === cat);
+             const allVisible = catMetrics.every(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key]);
+             const someVisible = catMetrics.some(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key]);
+             const isExpanded = expandedCategories[cat];
+ 
+             let statusClass = &#39;&#39;;
+             let iconName = &#39;circle-task&#39;;
+             if (allVisible) { statusClass = styles.active; iconName = &#39;accept&#39;; }
+             else if (someVisible) { statusClass = styles.partial; iconName = &#39;status-in-process&#39;; }
+ 
+             return (
+               &lt;div key={cat} className={styles.accordionGroup}&gt;
+                 &lt;div className={styles.accordionHeader}&gt;
+                   &lt;div
+                     className={styles.accordionTitle}
+                     onClick={() =&gt; toggleExpand(cat)}
+                   &gt;
+                     &lt;Icon
+                       name=&quot;slim-arrow-down&quot;
+                       size=&quot;small&quot;
+                       className={isExpanded ? styles.iconExpanded : styles.iconCollapsed}
+                     /&gt;
+                     &lt;span&gt;{cat}&lt;/span&gt;
+                   &lt;/div&gt;
+                   &lt;button
+                     className={&#96;${styles.categoryToggleBtn} ${statusClass}&#96;}
+                     onClick={(e) =&gt; {
+                       e.stopPropagation();
+                       onToggleCategory(cat);
+                     }}
+                     title={allVisible ? &quot;Hide All&quot; : &quot;Show All&quot;}
+                   &gt;
+                     &lt;Icon name={iconName} size=&quot;small&quot; /&gt;
+                   &lt;/button&gt;
+                 &lt;/div&gt;
+ 
+                 {isExpanded &amp;&amp; (
+                   &lt;div className={styles.accordionContent}&gt;
+                     {catMetrics.map(metric =&gt; {
+                       const isVisible = visibleMetrics[metric.key];
+                       const activeClass = isVisible ? styles.active : &#39;&#39;;
+ 
+                       return (
+                         &lt;button
+                           key={metric.key}
+                           className={&#96;${styles.metricBtn} ${activeClass}&#96;}
+                           onClick={() =&gt; onToggleMetric(metric.key)}
+                           style={{
+                             borderColor: isVisible ? metric.color : &#39;#ddd&#39;,
+                             background: isVisible ? &#96;${metric.color}15&#96; : &#39;white&#39;
+                           }}
+                         &gt;
+                           &lt;span style={{ color: isVisible ? metric.color : &#39;#95a5a6&#39; }}&gt;
+                             &lt;Icon name={isVisible ? &#39;show&#39; : &#39;hide&#39;} size=&quot;medium&quot; /&gt;
+                           &lt;/span&gt;
+                           &lt;div className={styles.metricInfo}&gt;
+                             &lt;div
+                               className={styles.metricName}
+                               style={{ color: isVisible ? metric.color : &#39;#95a5a6&#39; }}
+                             &gt;
+                               {metric.name}
+                             &lt;/div&gt;
+                             &lt;div className={styles.metricMeta}&gt;{metric.unit}&lt;/div&gt;
+                           &lt;/div&gt;
+                           &lt;div
+                             style={{
+                               width: &#39;20px&#39;,
+                               height: &#39;0&#39;,
+                               borderBottom: metric.strokeDasharray ? &#39;2px dashed&#39; : &#39;3px solid&#39;,
+                               borderColor: isVisible ? metric.color : &#39;#ddd&#39;
+                             }}
+                           /&gt;
+                         &lt;/button&gt;
+                       );
+                     })}
+                   &lt;/div&gt;
+                 )}
+               &lt;/div&gt;
+             );
+           })}
+         &lt;/div&gt;
+       &lt;/div&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;

+ import {
+   Chart as ChartJS,
+   CategoryScale,
+   LinearScale,
+   LineElement,
+   PointElement,
+   Title,
+   Tooltip,
+   Legend,
+ } from &#39;chart.js&#39;;
+ import { Line } from &#39;react-chartjs-2&#39;;
+ import { sacMetrics } from &#39;../../data/sacMetricsData&#39;;
+ import styles from &#39;../../styles/pages/SAC.module.css&#39;;
+ 
+ ChartJS.register(
+   CategoryScale,
+   LinearScale,
+   LineElement,
+   PointElement,
+   Title,
+   Tooltip,
+   Legend
+ );
+ 
+ function SACChart({ data, visibleMetrics, yAxisDomain }) {
+   const chartData = {
+     labels: data.map(d =&gt; d.day),
+     datasets: sacMetrics
+       .filter(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key])
+       .map(metric =&gt; ({
+         label: metric.name,
+         data: data.map(d =&gt; d[metric.key]),
+         borderColor: metric.color,
+         backgroundColor: metric.color,
+         borderWidth: metric.strokeWidth,
+         borderDash: metric.strokeDasharray || [],
+         pointRadius: metric.key === &#39;story_views&#39; ? 4 : 0,
+         pointHoverRadius: 6,
+         tension: 0.3,
+         fill: false
+       }))
+   };
+ 
+   const options = {
+     responsive: true,
+     maintainAspectRatio: false,
+     interaction: {
+       mode: &#39;index&#39;,
+       intersect: false,
+     },
+     plugins: {
+       legend: {
+         display: true,
+         position: &#39;bottom&#39;,
+         labels: {
+           usePointStyle: true,
+           boxWidth: 10
+         }
+       },
+       tooltip: {
+         backgroundColor: &#39;rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9)&#39;,
+         titleColor: &#39;#2c3e50&#39;,
+         bodyColor: &#39;#2c3e50&#39;,
+         borderColor: &#39;#ddd&#39;,
+         borderWidth: 1,
+         padding: 12,
+         callbacks: {
+           title: (context) =&gt; &#96;Day ${context[0].label}&#96;,
+           label: (context) =&gt; {
+             const metric = sacMetrics.find(m =&gt; m.name === context.dataset.label);
+             const value = typeof context.raw === &#39;number&#39; ? context.raw.toFixed(2) : context.raw;
+             return &#96;${context.dataset.label}: ${value} ${metric ? metric.unit : &#39;&#39;}&#96;;
+           }
+         }
+       }
+     },
+     scales: {
+       x: {
+         title: {
+           display: true,
+           text: &#39;Day of October 2025&#39;
+         },
+         grid: {
+           color: &#39;#ecf0f1&#39;
+         }
+       },
+       y: {
+         title: {
+           display: true,
+           text: &#39;Value (views, users, seconds, %)&#39;
+         },
+         grid: {
+           color: &#39;#ecf0f1&#39;
+         },
+         beginAtZero: true,
+         min: yAxisDomain[0] === &#39;auto&#39; ? undefined : yAxisDomain[0],
+         max: yAxisDomain[1] === &#39;auto&#39; ? undefined : yAxisDomain[1]
+       }
+     }
+   };
+ 
+   return (
+     &lt;div className={styles.sacChartContainer}&gt;
+       &lt;Line data={chartData} options={options} /&gt;
+     &lt;/div&gt;
+   );
+ }
+ 
+ export default SACChart;
+ 
```

+ import { useState, useMemo } from &#39;react&#39;;
+ import { generateSACData } from &#39;../../data/sacDataGenerator&#39;;
+ import { sacMetrics, sacCategories } from &#39;../../data/sacMetricsData&#39;;
+ 
+ export function useSACChart() {
+   const data = useMemo(() =&gt; generateSACData(), []);
+ 
+   // Initialize all metrics as visible
+   const [visibleMetrics, setVisibleMetrics] = useState(
+     sacMetrics.reduce((acc, m) =&gt; ({ ...acc, [m.key]: true }), {})
+   );
+ 
+   const [scale, setScale] = useState(&#39;auto&#39;);
+ 
+   // Toggle a single metric
+   const toggleMetric = (key) =&gt; {
+     setVisibleMetrics(prev =&gt; ({ ...prev, [key]: !prev[key] }));
+   };
+ 
+   // Toggle all metrics in a category
+   const toggleCategory = (category) =&gt; {
+     const catMetrics = sacMetrics.filter(m =&gt; m.category === category);
+     const allVisible = catMetrics.every(m =&gt; visibleMetrics[m.key]);
+ 
+     setVisibleMetrics(prev =&gt; {
+       const updated = { ...prev };
+       catMetrics.forEach(m =&gt; {
+         updated[m.key] = !allVisible;
+       });
+       return updated;
+     });
+   };
+ 
+   // Calculate y-axis domain based on visible metrics
+   const yAxisDomain = useMemo(() =&gt; {
+     if (scale === &#39;auto&#39;) {
+       return [&#39;auto&#39;, &#39;auto&#39;];
+     }
+ 
+     const visibleKeys = Object.keys(visibleMetrics).filter(k =&gt; visibleMetrics[k]);
+     if (visibleKeys.length === 0) return [0, 100];
+ 
+     let min = Infinity;
+     let max = -Infinity;
+ 
+     data.forEach(d =&gt; {
+       visibleKeys.forEach(key =&gt; {
+         const val = d[key];
+         if (typeof val === &#39;number&#39;) {
+           if (val &lt; min) min = val;
+           if (val &gt; max) max = val;
+         }
+       });
+     });
+ 
+     if (min === Infinity) min = 0;
+     if (max === -Infinity) max = 100;
+ 
+     const padding = (max - min) * 0.1;
+     return [Math.max(0, Math.floor(min - padding)), Math.ceil(max + padding)];
+   }, [data, visibleMetrics, scale]);
+ 
+   return {
+     data,
+     visibleMetrics,
+     scale,
+     setScale,
+     yAxisDomain,
+     toggleMetric,
+     toggleCategory
+   };
+ }
+
